Today is December 7, the 64th anniversiary of the Attack on Pearl Harbor. What most people don't realize, or selectivly choose to forget is that most Japanese auto makers were in the business of making Japanese warplanes that bombed Pearl Harbor, and killed Americans throughout the war. The most prominent of these was Mistubishi, mkaer of the Zero. Thats right, if you drive a Japanese car YOU SUPPORT THE BOMBING PEARL HARBOR, and YOU HATE AMERICA. So do the American thing, and burn you Japanese car. USA MOTHER$%^&*#



The above bit is just in jest, the Japnese have become one of America's greatest allies, but still you should never forget to remember what happened 64 years ago. So take time today to remember those who gave thier lives on this day so you wouldn't have to grow up speaking Japanese, Italian, or German.

Well today was Columbus day, or if you are Canadian it was thanksgiving. Why do we only celebrate columbus day, The Continent of North America was discovered by Leif Erikson, and he was a viking. Columbus was just a lame Italian navigator, who sailed under the Spanish Flag, and like all fashionable males of the Renaisance wore riduclous pataloons. Vikings on the other hand pillaged Europe from Britain to Constantinople, and ran around with battle axes killing people because they felt like it. They were better seamen than anybody of their day, and sailed to America the hard way, through the north Atlantic which is filled with icebergs. Face it Columbus was a pansy compared to Lief Erikson. We should be celebrating his day instead of Columbus (who got lost on his way to China, smooth move). So write your congressman, riot in the streets, and demand we celebrate the accomplishments of a real man, not some fancy pants looser who cant find Asia on a map.

So I'm sitting in GERM 121 like i do every MTWF at 10:10-11:00, and before class starts my Herr Buerstner asks if anyone has any questions. So I raise my hand and ask "Do Germans really love David Hasselhoff?". Since He is form Germany, he would definitely be able to answer this question. At first he stared at me for a little bit, and then he explained that Hasselhoff was very popular in Germany during the late 80's and the early 90's. He also stated that he had a Hasselhoff CD in his car, and listened to it regularly.I know a lot of you have probably pondered this at some point, and you might have even lost sleep over this. So you can sleep well now. It is true GERMANS LOVE DAVID HASSELHOFF.

Got bored this afternoon. Labor day and no class. Decided to go running. It was a very enlightening time, I ran for over 2 and a half hours today. A lot has been on my mind recently. College life is great and all, but  I have a strange feeling I am not going anywhere with my life though. I have been thinking a lot about enlisting and going to Iraq. I want to do something with my life, and be a part of history. I suppourt the war to a certain extent, and feel It is my obligation to put up or shut up. Other people are over there putting their life on the line for me and the rest of America, maybe it is my time to do the same. Sure there is the chance if I go I might not come back, but that doesn't seem to bother me. as Sir William Wallace once said "Every man dies, not every man truly lives"

I got a package in the mail today from one of my friends in Raleigh. He sent me the greatest poster ever  to hang on my dorm room wall. Turns out he was able to find a poster of the Original Lionforce Voltron. Yes Voltron The Defender of the Universe. If you are asking yourself " WTF is Voltron???" you need to get a life real fast. To answer that question Voltron was the greatest thing to come out of the 80's, even better than Ninja Turtles and Transformers COMBINED. If the US was to ever build Voltron, the War on Terrorism would end immdiatly. No raghead would ever even think about pissing America off if we had Voltron. Man that would be so awesome.

I just got  finished talking to my cousin who lives, well lived would be more appropriate now, in Gulfport MS. If you have followed CNN or any other news source you would know that this area has been almost completly obliterated. They don't even have enough refrigerated trucks to remove the corpses of the dead. He decided to ride out the Hurricane in his home because "Thre is no way that hurricane will kill me, it has a girls name. No one in the Rish family will ever be killed by a pansy girl hurricane." he told this to my uncle Sunday. Well his house no longer exists, and he almost died after his house flooded. He survived by clinging to debris from his neighbors house, who he said are missing.  The first thing he told me was, "I kicked that hurricanes ass, there isn't a storm out there that could take me alive". He has finaly gotten out of there, and is with friends in Tennesee Even with all of the death and destruction brought by this storm I could not help but laugh as my cousin described the experience. Here is a man who probably should of died, but by sheer dumb luck he survived. I am proud to be related to this man. Most people would wet their pants just by hearing his story of what wnet on, but he revels in the fact that he was almost killed.

I only had 3 hrs of sleep last night. The sleeves on the penetrate and dominate shirt are a little too short for my taste, so I'm am going to have to pass it on.  The clothes I am wearing reak of frebreze and my own funk. I dont have any clean boxers, so I have been weraing the same pair for two days. All I have eaten today was a poptart, a ham sandwich, and a hot pocket. But life could not be better. I only have one class on thursday at 9:00 untill 10:25, so I played video games all afternoon. Yeah I may be hungry, tired, and have a scent that would kill a wild yak at 300 yards, but I have never been better. Last year at college pretty much sucked. It hasn't been utill I came to USC that I really realized what college was about. Football is seven days away, and things look good this season. I see people on campus that i know from elsewhere, which didn't happen last year. You have no idea what it means to me to see people I went to high school with around campus. I have a room that isn't growing copius amounts of mold, and don't have to worry about raccons attacking me from trashcans. The campus has buildings that aren't made of brick.( sidenote all of the buildings on NC State's campus was made of the exact same type of red brick, you could literally feel your soul being sucked out of you) I finally know why college is supposed to be the best time of my life. GO GAMECOCKS.

Thats about the only thing interesting that hass happened in a while. This morning I woke up to my suitemate  yelling how someone stole his bike. Well the whole bike wasn't stolen. Damn, today was one crazy day. They started distributing tickets for the first game against UCF. It took over 2 hours in line, but it was worth it for the simple reason it was for FOOTBALL. I can't wait for the season to get started. It will at least break the monotony of going to class. College life has been gret so far. By having to opurtunity to go to 2 different schools, I was able to see things a lot differently. However after all the of the changes that has happened since I went to school some things never change. I still have my clothes all over the floor in several piles. I skip showering every so often just to get 5 extra minutes of sleep. Life has been good for the most part. I think I have a legitimate shot of getting an A in all of my classes this semester.

Friday I got a letter from the HQ USAFR. Apparantly I have been relived of my position as an A1C in the Air Force Reserve, and have been honorably discharged from service. I had no idea that because I was on scholarship for ROTC last year that I was an actual Airman 1st Class in the Air Force Reserve, and didn't know it untill I was discharged. This technically makes me a veteran of the Air Force Reserve. Isn't that wierd?

If you have spent at least 2 maybe 3 seconds in college you probably know how ridiculosly expensive books are. Well today being the day before classes start I realized i probably need to by my books. Well I had to 3 different bookstores around campus to get what I needed. In total I spent $445.75. My grandparents were nice enough to give me $450 for this semester to spend, and well after today I have enogh of that left to eat at Taco bell. Apparantly it's really cool to make each student buy 5 textbooks for a class, all of them printed brand new so you can't get used ones. Probably I'll get $10 back at the end of the semester, because a new edition of all my books just came out that had a total of two sentences changed in it, and a new picture on the cover. Maybe I should go into a carrer of writing text books, I could become amazingly rich by doing maybe 3hrs. of work an entire year. Well thats enough ranting for one day. Time to actulally put my clothes in the drawers, since they have been in a pile on the floor since saturday. Hopefully I can keep them in the drawers for longer than 2 weeks this time. But if you haver ever seen my room at home, you know there is no way that will ever happen.
